com.vector.cfg.model.access

Interface IReferenceAccess


  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public interface IReferenceAccess

    IReferenceAccess

    The IReferenceAccess is a basic model service which provides methods to simplify reference handling.
    • getRefTarget(MIARRef): Returns the target object, an AUTOSAR reference points to. This method works for all reference types and therefore returns an object of type MIReferrable. This is the base type all reference target types must implement
    • getReferenceTarget(MIReferenceValue): Returns the target object of a reference-value (ECUC parameter of type MIReferenceValue)
    • sortReferences(Collection): Sorts a collection of AUTOSAR references to guarantee deterministic order for example during code generation (the sort criteria are described in the JavaDoc documentation in the code).
    • getAllReferencesPointingTo(MIReferrable): This is the reverse operation of getRefTarget(MIARRef)
    • getReferenceParametersPointingTo(MIReferrable): This is the reverse operation of getReferenceTarget(MIReferenceValue)
    All AUTOSAR reference objects in the MDF model have the base interface MIARRef. Figure shows this type hierarchy for the definition reference of an ECUC container.

    In ARXML, such a reference can be specified as: 

     <DEFINITION-REF DEST="ECUC-PARAM-CONF-CONTAINER-DEF">
     /MIRCOSAR/Com/ComGeneral
 </DEFINITION-REF>
    • MIARRef.getValue() returns the AUTOSAR path of the object, the reference points to (as specified in the ARXML file). In the example above "/MIRCOSAR/Com/ComGeneral" would be this value
    • MIContainerDefARRef#getRefTarget() on the other hand returns the referenced MDF object if it exists. This method is located in a specific, typesafe (according to the type it points to) reference interface which extends MIARRef. So, if an object with the AUTOSAR path "/MIRCOSAR/Com/ComGeneral" exists in the model, this method will return it

    This ProjectService is threadsafe

java.util.List<com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.model.autosar.ecucdescription.MIParameterValue> getActiveEcucParametersPointingTo(com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.commoncore.autosar.MIReferrable target)
        This method returns all parameter objects located in the ActiveEcuC which are parent objects or references pointing to the specified target. It returns an empty collection if the object is invisible, removed or null.

      • getReferenceTarget

        @PublishedMethod
com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.commoncore.autosar.MIReferrable getReferenceTarget(com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.model.autosar.ecucdescription.MIReferenceValue parameter)
        This method returns the target object of the specified reference parameter. It returns null in the following cases:
        • No such target exists
        • If the parameter is null
        • If the parameter is removed or invisible
        Parameters:
        parameter -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        MultipleVariantObjectsException - if more than one reference target exists which can never happen in the following cases:
        • In non-variant projects
        • If the client code is being executed in a predefined variant view

        This method returns all target objects of the specified reference parameter. It returns an empty collection in the following cases:

      • sortReferences

        @PublishedMethod
<T extends com.vector.cfg.model.mdf.commoncore.autosar.MIARRef> java.util.List<T> sortReferences(java.util.Collection<T> references)
        This method sorts the specified collection of reference objects to guarantee deterministic order.

        The criterion to be sorted by is the object link of the reference objects. If this link is equal, the reference values (AUTOSAR path) will be compared.

        Parameters:
        references -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified collection is null
